<br>
NO this VERY Honorable and kindhearted person went above and beyond all that.<br>
<br>
I am going to leave out a few details that I feel dont need to be brought up here but will only say that everyone involved in this are nothing but the best of people and I wished the ALL lived right next door or down the street from me. I would even be proud to call these people family.<br>
<br>
I had in RL made a big move, extremely far away from my northern new england surroundings where I was born and raised. And as happens sometimes things just didnt work out for me so I wanted to go back home.<br>
<br>
But murphys law wasn't done with me yet. There I was without transportation and digging through the cobwebs of my wallet for the last of my cash, I went to go rent a vehicle to carry me and my few meger belongings back home when my CC went poof no more was deactivated hehe thats what i get for sharing one with a family member and they dont pay the bill.<br>
<br>
So I could't get anything to get my belongings back home with me stuck halfway across the country, I always find comfort and a extremely kind ear in the friends I have made here to listen to my problems weather they are Eq related or RL ones.I logged on and found my only friend who was on for that time of day and was telling him what was bothering me, and suddenly i get a &quot; before you do ANYTHING hold on a min bro I got to talk to my wife .&quot;<br>
<br>
I thought maybe she had called him away or something as we all get called AFK here and there. Well much to my suprise  he tells me out of the blue and totally unexpected that HE will come and get me ( an 8 hour drive from where he lived to where I was ) and then he will drive halfway across the country to get me home.And then to only turn around and drive himself BACK to his home.<br>
<br>
I was in SHOCK !!! to say the least , I had to double check and he was serious about the offer.Though our trip wasnt fast to get home there was good reason we made a few stops along the way, On my jouney I got to meet his lovely and extremely nice wife ( one of the luckies men I know ) and thier two babies ( pair of rottweillers like my baby ) and along the way we also stopped and met and enjoyed the kind hospitality of a few others in his guild ( which im proud to say i was made an honorary member long ago ) who are some of the nicest people I have met even better than some of the people from my own hometown.<br>
<br>
It really makes you ( or me ) think now people can and do act one way behind the safety of the keyboard but can be totally different in RL and him and all of those met on my journey  have shown me that they ARE what they ARE.Hehe now even my own family thinks tha is more than JUST a game.<br>
<br>
So if you ever get online and see or meet an iskar monk named .............KAZITA BLACKBELT...............................<br>
know that he IS an honorable man on both sides of that keyboard and would never do anyone any harm or wrong doings.<br>
<br>
